com.twitter.heron.network

Class MetricsManagerClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.twitter.heron.common.network.HeronClient
      • com.twitter.heron.network.MetricsManagerClient
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ISelectHandler

    public class MetricsManagerClient
extends HeronClient
    MetricsClient implements SocketClient and communicate with Metrics Manager, it will: 1. Check whether we got a PhysicalPlanHelper in singletonRegistry, and if we got one we will send the register request; so it will not send registerRequest directly when it is connected 2. Handle relative response for register request 3. It will no need call the onIncomingMessage(), since it will not accept any message
